<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Codeberg on NeoTech Club's Blog</title><link>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/categories/codeberg/</link><description>Recent content in Codeberg on NeoTech Club's Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 05:44:31 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/categories/codeberg/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Git Workshop 1 -&gt; Level 3: Making Changes to Other People's Repos(Route B: Codeberg)</title><link>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-3-making-changes-to-other-peoples-reposroute-b-codeberg/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 05:44:31 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-3-making-changes-to-other-peoples-reposroute-b-codeberg/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="git-workshop-1"&gt;Git Workshop 1
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id="level-3-sending-pull-requests"&gt;Level 3: Sending Pull Requests
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="step-0-log-in-to-your-codeberg-account"&gt;Step 0: Log in to your codeberg account
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h3 id="step-1-go-to-the-repo"&gt;Step 1: Go to the repo
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a class="link" href="https://codeberg.org/neotechclub/git-playground" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://codeberg.org/neotechclub/git-playground&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-2-fork-the-repository"&gt;Step 2: Fork the Repository
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img width="298" height="299" alt="fork button in codeberg" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/55c61845-d1e3-4eee-94e9-e5294aff9d97" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change repository name if you&amp;rsquo;d like. We suggest leaving it as-is!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="300" height="299" alt="repo name box in fork review screen" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3d727fd9-7066-486e-92d2-7b66686773c9" /&gt;
&lt;img width="302" height="298" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7de1fad1-599b-430b-9b7e-772525c319a8" /&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-3-making-the-change"&gt;Step 3: Making the change
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Notice that the repo you copied is now &amp;ldquo;forked&amp;rdquo; in your name? This can be used as a personal copy of the repo including all the changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is also used to submit a &amp;ldquo;Pull Request&amp;rdquo;! It can also be called a &amp;ldquo;Merge Request&amp;rdquo; or a &amp;ldquo;PR&amp;rdquo;. Click on the pencil icon to edit the document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="303" height="299" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/616bd0a0-a48f-44cd-a7a8-54a2563a30ac" /&gt;
&lt;img width="296" height="293" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e2980c81-b4e9-48c6-aece-572c6a27eb05" /&gt;
&lt;img width="296" height="297" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fa1a7f62-f5db-4784-b8a6-8a068fe4edee" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instructions: Add some text. Something simple with your name like &amp;ldquo;&lt;yourname&gt; was here!&amp;rdquo; is recommended!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add commit data like title and maybe description(optional, but recommended!)
&lt;img width="302" height="301" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e92d77eb-1dd8-458d-a8b1-01bda559bb6b" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember to finish by committing your changes!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="298" height="297" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f0aaa7ee-75b1-4321-92a4-2118b406564f" /&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-4-submit-your-change-as-a-pull-request"&gt;Step 4: Submit your change as a Pull Request!
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Head back over to the main repository at &lt;a class="link" href="https://codeberg.org/neotechclub/git-playground" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://codeberg.org/neotechclub/git-playground&lt;/a&gt; and go to pull requests page&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img width="295" height="294" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/648ae184-4cb3-4bf5-82ec-53bee5f08ca5" /&gt;
&lt;img width="294" height="295" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d813bab7-3f80-46ce-9f16-53cabb861658" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a new pull request and select your repository&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="300" height="296" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d2472c7c-0239-45af-9269-0f31310c09ac" /&gt;
&lt;img width="298" height="302" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/52dcef2b-bced-4106-ba02-bdc9a2bf2de0" /&gt;
&lt;img width="296" height="300" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c3644414-aeeb-467b-82cc-93c24f4229b7" /&gt;
&lt;img width="301" height="294" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cd144b7e-ec27-4888-8e2d-3af5429eb9f0" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review your pull request message.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure you do this in a professional way because this is the first thing most people see when they come across your PR!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="299" height="299" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/61c9cd20-bcce-45f4-906f-e9e87f1598f9" /&gt;
&lt;img width="294" height="297" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d6475ec8-8157-4e2b-a754-39b38e66c40b" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engage in further discussion if you&amp;rsquo;d like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img width="296" height="298" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f6be3ff0-90f6-40d5-8467-63c3adb05ff5" /&gt;</description></item><item><title>Git Workshop 1 -&gt; Level 2: Making a Repository (Route B: Codeberg)</title><link>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-2-making-a-repository-route-b-codeberg/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 05:43:48 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-2-making-a-repository-route-b-codeberg/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="git-workshop-1"&gt;Git Workshop 1
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id="level-2-making-your-first-repository"&gt;Level 2: Making your first repository
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="step-0-ensure-youre-logged-into-codeberg"&gt;Step 0: Ensure you&amp;rsquo;re logged into codeberg
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h3 id="step-1-prepare-to-create-a-new-repository"&gt;Step 1: Prepare to create a new repository
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a general rule of thumb, &lt;code&gt;+&lt;/code&gt; symbol usually indicates that something can be created and ‚úèsymbol indicates that something can be edited!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="300" height="299" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5fe064b8-06c1-4035-8887-3fd5c11eaffc" /&gt;
&lt;img width="298" height="299" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1c035d0a-5850-4334-bc50-1b20840885d2" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure you&amp;rsquo;re logged in as the correct user!
&lt;img width="302" height="299" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6491c702-26f0-4eb6-89f3-6aee44b599ee" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-2-describe-and-create-your-repository"&gt;Step 2: Describe and Create your Repository
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some suggestions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be descriptive and clear
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good: customer-support-app&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bad: repo-new&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use lowercase
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good: my-project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bad: My-Project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use hyphens as separators (slug-case)
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good: my-project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bad: my_project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avoid special characters
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use only letters, numbers, and hyphens&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep it short and concise
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shorter names are easier to remember&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avoid version numbers
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use tags for versions (e.g., v1.0.0)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bad: invoice-generator-v2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will have ample opportunities to version our code with branches and tags!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;img width="294" height="296" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a168e46d-b77a-4ec3-86bb-bd013f1db415" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optionally, make repository private. This means that your friends cannot see your work! That wasn&amp;rsquo;t very Open Source of you &amp;gt;:(&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="293" height="296" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9bb846ea-bea0-4a12-a4d2-b0a7137e2fe6" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add an appropriate description to convey what your repo does&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img width="302" height="298" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8cce0f5d-be07-4b3a-8077-a480100dc19c" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;remember to select this for the next step!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="302" height="293" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b874ef32-8d1b-4592-bed1-e7235520bbe1" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember to create your repository!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="294" height="298" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc1e7711-7b07-41c1-9e9a-0ca9c1ea5c6e" /&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-3-edit-your-first-file-readmemd"&gt;Step 3: Edit your first file: README.md
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img width="299" height="301" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc8d8ab9-a814-46bc-9e89-b205179b0bc0" /&gt;
&lt;img width="303" height="297" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/abdcafa9-bd40-4a3d-b576-b0039c05026a" /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the file most people see when they first view your repository, even non programmers. This should contain a good introductory piece of documentation for what your repo/code does, how to use it, etc. Ensure this is professional and good!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="299" height="295" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c98a72ad-046c-4a89-834f-b02464be0209" /&gt;
&lt;img width="298" height="296" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/28b913cd-1abc-437b-9d8a-8f50316d1588" /&gt;
&lt;img width="306" height="293" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/809ad03f-f24d-4afa-8e67-4a6b0f97dfd0" /&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-4-saving-your-file-using-commits"&gt;Step 4: Saving your file using Commits
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;With git, we use &amp;ldquo;commits&amp;rdquo; to track changes. Each commit(a snapshot of the repository) has a change title, description, and a hash ID. This makes code management for non-insignificant projects very simple!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most git services and git cli provide(s) a diff-like view that shows changes in a before-after form side-by-side.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember to add a descriptive and relevant commit message here!
&lt;img width="299" height="297" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f298e640-27d5-4bd8-b6c9-c0dd7b0b0b42" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember to actually finish committing your changes! You can check the history tab afterwards to see what your commit changed!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img width="300" height="300" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/135b836f-a744-476d-a657-4703571906ca" /&gt;</description></item><item><title>Git Workshop 1 -&gt; Level 1: Making a Codeberg Account (Route B: Codeberg)</title><link>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-1-making-a-codeberg-account-route-b-codeberg/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 05:42:20 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.neotechclub.qzz.io/p/git-workshop-1-level-1-making-a-codeberg-account-route-b-codeberg/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Git Workshop 1
Level 1: Making your Codeberg account&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-0-prepare-an-email-for-this-workshop"&gt;Step 0: Prepare an email for this workshop
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feel free to use your existing mail ID&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guide is using Proton Mail on android but you can follow this with almost any provider, like gmail, outlook, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-1-open-codeberg"&gt;Step 1: Open Codeberg
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a class="link" href="https://codeberg.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://codeberg.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-2-register"&gt;Step 2: Register
